<subSubSection id="C37A14E8FF83FFC6FF3F0446FF4BF811" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF3F0446FF4BF811" blockId="2.[136,1452,1148,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FF3F0446FE75F880" bold="true" box="[189,495,1868,1894]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Until now, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FCE70446FBEDF880" box="[869,1143,1868,1894]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FCE70446FBEDF880" box="[869,1143,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Passiflora caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be restricted to PNC (
<figureCitation id="135B5BE6FF83FFC6FF4D047AFE8EF86C" box="[207,276,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[136,229,855,877]" captionTargetBox="[352,1236,203,818]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[340,1247,190,831]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution map of Passiflora caparaoensis and P. campanulata. BA= Bahia, ES= Espírito Santo, GO= Goiás, MT= Mato Grosso, MS= Mato Grosso do Sul, MG= Minas Gerais, PR= Paraná, RJ= Rio de Janeiro, RS= Rio Grande do Sul, SC= Santa Catarina, SP= São Paulo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534633/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, blue dots). This known population occurs at an elevation of approximately 
<quantity id="4C98EA86FF83FFC6FBF8047AFADEF86C" box="[1146,1348,1904,1931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0949999999999998" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.9899999999999998" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" unit="m" value="2095.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1990.0">1,990 to 2,200 m</quantity>
.a.s.l. in a cloud forest, in the transition area between high montane ombrophilous forest and high-altitude grassland, near the riverbed. In this environment, temperatures can be extremely low throughout the year (reaching ca. min 4ºC) (ICMBio 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF1F17EBFF82FFC7FF0A044EFAEEF898" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534625" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6534625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534625/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" startId="3.[136,229,1860,1882]" targetBox="[152,1436,220,1820]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF82FFC7FF0A044EFAEEF898" blockId="3.[136,1452,1860,1918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF82FFC7FF0A044EFF64F8BF" bold="true" box="[136,254,1860,1882]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF82FFC7FE86044EFE77F8BC" box="[260,493,1860,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF82FFC7FE86044EFE77F8BC" box="[260,493,1860,1882]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Passiflora caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A. leaf, B. branch, C. Stipules, D. longitudinal cut of the flower, E. detail of operculum and limen, F. Bracts (
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF82FFC7FF690463FDB1F89B" box="[235,555,1896,1918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">A.M. Moraes &amp; A.P.G. Faria 376</emphasis>
), G. seed, H. fruit (
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF82FFC7FD6A0463FBAEF89B" box="[744,1076,1896,1918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">A.M. Moraes &amp; R.F. Tiburtino 381</emphasis>
). Drawn by Andreza M. Moraes.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C37A14E8FF82FFC7FF3F04A7FB44F80D" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF82FFC7FF3F04A7FB44F80D" blockId="3.[136,1451,1965,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF82FFC7FF3F04A7FED2F821" bold="true" box="[189,328,1965,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The name of the new species refers to the location of its record, known as the region of Caparaó, between 
<collectingRegion id="49A48981FF82FFC7FF6E04DBFE18F80D" box="[236,386,2001,2027]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49A48981FF82FFC7FE3B04DBFDC3F80D" box="[441,601,2001,2027]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
states, and that gives the name to Caparaó National Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF1F17EBFF85FFC0FF0A0795FE34FAA3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534629" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6534629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534629/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" startId="4.[136,229,1183,1205]" targetBox="[314,1274,196,1152]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF85FFC0FF0A0795FE34FAA3" blockId="4.[136,1452,1183,1349]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FF0A0795FF65FB52" bold="true" box="[136,255,1183,1205]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FE840795FE6DFB53" box="[262,503,1183,1205]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF85FFC0FE840795FE69FB53" box="[262,499,1183,1205]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">Passiflora caparaoensis</taxonomicName>
