</emphasis>
A. branch with leaves, stipules and tendrils (
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FC3307AAFA9EFB53" box="[945,1284,1183,1205]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">A.M. Moraes &amp; R.F. Tiburtino 381</emphasis>
), B. detail of the petiole without glands and base dentate gland-tipped leaves, C. detail of the surface abaxial of stipule, D. surface adaxial of leaves, E. surface abaxial of leaves, F. branch with leaves, floral buds and tendrils, G. detail of the bracts, H. old bracts, I. ovary, J. detail of the operculum and limen (
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FEE00606FD32FAC6" box="[354,680,1291,1313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">A.M. Moraes &amp; A.P.G. Faria 376</emphasis>
), K. fruit (
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FC930606FBC7FAC7" box="[785,1117,1291,1313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">A.M. Moraes &amp; R.F. Tiburtino 381</emphasis>
). Photography by Ana Paula G. de Faria and Andreza M. Moraes.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C37A14E8FF85FFC0FF3F067EFE9CFA54" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF85FFC0FF3F067EFE9CFA54" blockId="4.[136,1452,1396,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FF3F067EFED9FA68" bold="true" box="[189,323,1396,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Phenology:</emphasis>
—This species was collected with buds, flowers and fruits in January and with flowers in September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A14E8FF85FFC0FF3F06B1FB97F980" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF85FFC0FF3F06B1FB97F980" blockId="4.[136,1452,1396,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FF3F06B1FE2CFA30" bold="true" box="[189,438,1467,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—Critically Endangered (CR). The observed population of 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF85FFC0FBDD06B7FA88FA30" box="[1119,1298,1469,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FBDD06B7FA88FA30" box="[1119,1298,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">P. caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains less than ten mature individuals. In its occurrence area, we found the presence of an invasive species of fern, 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF85FFC0FAB906EAFF60F9F8" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF85FFC0FAB906EAFF60F9F8" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Pteridium aquilinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Kunth (1879: 11), and a continuous flow of tourists. At present, we are not aware of any other locality where this species persists. Therefore, we suggest that the species can be categorized as CR, considering the very small or restricted population with less than 50 individuals (criterion D) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF13A92FF85FFC0FCF50546FB9BF980" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[887,1025,1612,1638]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" refId="ref6456" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2022) Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 15. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 116 pp. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 24 April 2022)" type="book" year="2022">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
